.TH "ipu_init_channel_buffer" 9 "ipu_init_channel_buffer" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ipu_init_channel_buffer \- initialize a buffer for logical IPU channel.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ipu_init_channel_buffer
.BI "(struct idmac_channel *ichan "  ","
.BI "enum pixel_fmt pixel_fmt "  ","
.BI "uint16_t width "  ","
.BI "uint16_t height "  ","
.BI "uint32_t stride "  ","
.BI "enum ipu_rotate_mode rot_mode "  ","
.BI "dma_addr_t phyaddr_0 "  ","
.BI "dma_addr_t phyaddr_1 "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ichan" 12
IDMAC channel.
.IP "pixel_fmt" 12
pixel format of buffer. Pixel format is a FOURCC ASCII code.
.IP "width" 12
width of buffer in pixels.
.IP "height" 12
height of buffer in pixels.
.IP "stride" 12
stride length of buffer in pixels.
.IP "rot_mode" 12
rotation mode of buffer. A rotation setting other than
IPU_ROTATE_VERT_FLIP should only be used for input buffers of
rotation channels.
.IP "phyaddr_0" 12
buffer 0 physical address.
.IP "phyaddr_1" 12
buffer 1 physical address. Setting this to a value other than
NULL enables double buffering mode.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success or negative error code on failure.
